          "body": "Acts 5:29 — 'We must obey God rather than men' — is the load-bearing sentence of the chapter and the charter for every subsequent moment of Christian civil disobedience in history. But Luke embeds it in a narrative that prevents misuse. Peter is not asserting autonomy; he is asserting that the God of the fathers, who raised Jesus and exalted Him, has commissioned the apostolic witness, and no human authority can countermand that commission. The same chapter that grounds the principle (5:29) ends with the cost (5:40-41) and the persistence (5:42). Obedience to God when men forbid is not a posture of defiance but a posture of worship — and Luke ensures we see it produces flogging, joy, and daily preaching in the same breath."
